The set of variables:
read.table(): reads a file in table format and creates a data frame from it
colnames():  set the column names of a matrix-like object
cbind()/rbind(): take a sequence of vector, matrix or data-frame arguments and combine by columns or rows, respectively
grepl(): search for matches to argument pattern within each element of a character vector
join(): similarly to merge()
gsub(): perform replacement of all matches
make.names(): make syntactically valid names out of character vectors
ddply(): for each subset of a data frame, apply function then combine results into a data frame
write.table(): prints its required argument x to a file
